					<h2 class="mb-4">From the Buyer’s side</h2>
					<p class="mb-5">Denial of receiving the product: if you want to deny of receiving the product, you can complain that products or part of the products that you purchased is completely missing or parts of the product are missing.
					As a solution, firstly you can file this case to the Dinger team to investigate and refund process for the product.
					Secondly, the Dinger team will check with the store owner that it is a valid request or not. It may take at most 21 days to be resolved.
					</p>

					<h2 class="mb-4">Fake return</h2>
					<p class="mb-5">You file about the return but you don’t return the products or parts of the product. Dinger will control this case by defining the return process. We will have our official partner for returning the product. We will investigate together with our partner. That could take up to <b>21</b> days to resolve.</p>

					<h2 class="mb-4">Demand to refund after the purchase</h2>
					<p class="mb-5">You purchased and completed the transaction but you demand to refund. As a clarification, Dinger will get consent from the user that nothing can be refunded after the purchase unless fake items or fake description. If the product is in those stages, you can file a case to the Dinger team.</p>

					<h2 class="mb-4">From the Seller’s side, Unmatch product</h2>
					<p class="mb-5">Products that are not matched with their description (showcase on the Dinger interface). Store Owners sell the product with description but fail to deliver the exact detail description of those products or fake products. End customer needs to file a case to be investigated by the Dinger team. It will take up to <b>21</b> days. If the store owner is doing the fraud, we will terminate the contract.</p>

					<h2 class="mb-4">Misusing Dinger Brand</h2>
					<p class="mb-5">Store owners imitate the payment method of Dinger purposely to take the data of customers’ payment information or any other information. As a solution, Users have to accept the terms and conditions of the Dinger team. In that, we will have a statement that the user has to check that the URL is correct or not. If it is not a correct URL, the consequences will be responsible by the user. They can come and check that URL on the Dinger website.
					<b>Acting as Dinger</b>: Store owners claim that they are using Dinger but they are not (but registered in Dinger) and charging extra transaction charges from customers. In user terms and conditions, we will add the statement that if the user didn’t use the link from Dinger, Dinger is not responsible for any consequences.
